77
00:04:54,388 --> 00:04:56,085
Helena Davison signing in.

78
00:04:56,116 --> 00:04:58,357
Send all tidbits, gossip welcome.

79
00:04:58,388 --> 00:05:01,268
Hot off the griddle. Kay Strong,
the first to be married to Harald,

80
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:04,277
with an "A," Peterson, a
budding genius of the theater.

81
00:05:04,308 --> 00:05:06,676
The day, June 10th, the place, St.
Mark's Church,

82
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:07,924
St. Mark's Place, New York.

83
00:05:07,956 --> 00:05:09,204
Really, Helena.

84
00:05:09,236 --> 00:05:13,044
Invitations orally by the
bride, no parents present.

85
00:05:13,076 --> 00:05:14,804
Most unconventional.

86
00:05:14,837 --> 00:05:16,916
Harald Peterson.

87
00:05:17,556 --> 00:05:18,612
Who'd a thunk it?

88
00:05:20,116 --> 00:05:22,260
A church wedding, hah?

89
00:05:22,292 --> 00:05:24,276
Kay, the scoffer and atheist.

90
00:05:25,172 --> 00:05:27,060
She would.

91
00:05:27,092 --> 00:05:28,724
She'll introduce him as a Yale man.

92
00:05:28,756 --> 00:05:30,580
He only did a little graduate work in drama.

93
00:05:30,612 --> 00:05:33,620
Typical of Kay, used to drive us wild.

94
00:05:33,652 --> 00:05:35,700
But Kay's a darling.

95
00:05:35,732 --> 00:05:38,004
Mother, Kay has been living
with Harald for a year.

96
00:05:38,036 --> 00:05:40,244
Weekends in New York, even flaunting it.

97
00:05:40,276 --> 00:05:42,420
Libby, we've got to get organized.

98
00:05:42,452 --> 00:05:44,084
<i>Wedding presents first.</i>

99
00:05:44,116 --> 00:05:45,684
<i>Individual or one from all of us?</i>

100
00:05:45,716 --> 00:05:47,764
No, one from all of us.
So much cheaper that way.

101
00:05:47,796 --> 00:05:50,036
What about a reception?
Has Kay decided anything?

102
00:05:50,068 --> 00:05:52,404
She's been angling like mad
for Pokey's townhouse.

103
00:05:53,556 --> 00:05:55,059
Very posh, she'll love that.

104
00:05:55,092 --> 00:05:57,844
Or next best, Long Island, the Prisses.

105
00:05:57,876 --> 00:06:00,404
Much as I'd love to do it for Kay, Priss,

106
00:06:00,436 --> 00:06:04,051
your own wedding so soon now is all
a poor widow woman can manage.

107
00:06:04,756 --> 00:06:06,835
Mother!

108
00:06:06,868 --> 00:06:09,300
What's the problem? Have them come up here.
How many? Twenty?

109
00:06:09,332 --> 00:06:11,508
I've cooked for 50 in my time.

110
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:14,036
With a staff of ten, Henry.

111
00:06:14,068 --> 00:06:15,988
That's sweet of you, Father, but

112
00:06:16,020 --> 00:06:18,580
it's too far, Harald has to be
back at the theater that evening.

113
00:06:19,219 --> 00:06:20,756
No honeymoon?

114
00:06:20,787 --> 00:06:22,996
Who thinks of honeymoons these days, Mother?

115
00:06:23,028 --> 00:06:25,396
Especially if you've already had it.

116
00:06:25,427 --> 00:06:28,659
Since there's only two days left and
Kay hasn't decided anything yet.

117
00:06:28,692 --> 00:06:30,579
And we know that she can't
afford it, then Mother and I...

118
00:06:30,612 --> 00:06:31,860
Hold it, dear, she has.

119
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:34,196
She just called, a wedding breakfast.

120
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:35,508
She and Harald are throwing it.

121
00:06:35,539 --> 00:06:37,268
<i>It's so much nicer that way.</i>

122
00:06:37,299 --> 00:06:39,348
Really, Dottie, so much nicer.

123
00:06:54,068 --> 00:06:55,699
Who are they?

124
00:06:55,732 --> 00:06:57,107
The groom's team.

125
00:07:04,755 --> 00:07:06,548
Who's the good-looker?

126
00:07:06,579 --> 00:07:07,796
Harald's painter friend.

127
00:07:07,827 --> 00:07:09,043
The neighbor?

128
00:07:09,076 --> 00:07:11,540
And Kay's, dear, on weekends.

129
00:07:14,259 --> 00:07:15,796
Where is the breakfast?

130
00:07:15,827 --> 00:07:17,267
Brevoort.

131
00:07:17,908 --> 00:07:19,795
Charming old hotel.

132
00:07:19,828 --> 00:07:21,427
So much more appropriate,
don't you think, Libby?

133
00:07:21,459 --> 00:07:22,643
What?

134
00:07:22,675 --> 00:07:24,307
Kay giving the breakfast.

135
00:07:24,339 --> 00:07:27,156
City Hall would have been more
appropriate too, I think.

136
00:07:27,187 --> 00:07:30,323
Instead of trying to carry off a
wedding in Peter Stuyvesant's church.

137
00:07:30,355 --> 00:07:32,499
Harald not to the manor born, exactly.

138
00:07:41,171 --> 00:07:43,827
Doesn't she know a black hat
is bad luck for weddings?

139
00:07:47,731 --> 00:07:51,603
Dearly beloved, we are gathered
together here in the sight of God...

140
00:07:51,635 --> 00:07:54,675
My God! Harald in brown suede shoes.

141
00:07:54,707 --> 00:07:55,859
Shut up.

142
00:07:56,755 --> 00:07:58,547
Into this holy estate,

143
00:07:58,579 --> 00:08:01,075
these two persons present
come now to be joined.

144
00:08:01,907 --> 00:08:04,243
If any man can show just cause

145
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:06,995
why they may not be
lawfully joined together,

146
00:08:07,027 --> 00:08:11,603
let him now speak or else
hereafter forever hold his peace.

147
00:08:11,635 --> 00:08:16,019
Katherine Leslie, wilt thou have
this man for thy wedded husband,

148
00:08:16,051 --> 00:08:18,515
to live together after God's ordinance

149
00:08:18,547 --> 00:08:20,435
in the holy estate of matrimony,

150
00:08:20,467 --> 00:08:22,355
so long as you both shall live?

151
00:08:22,387 --> 00:08:24,019
I will.

152
00:08:24,051 --> 00:08:25,426
Hey, Kay, we're going with you.

153
00:08:25,459 --> 00:08:27,027
Goodbye, everybody!

154
00:08:35,827 --> 00:08:38,643
I still think that we should have
done something about the reception.

155
00:08:38,675 --> 00:08:40,434
No, I don't agree.

156
00:08:40,467 --> 00:08:43,699
There's certainly no need to
encourage Kay's pretensions.

157
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:45,107
How hard you can be, Lakey.

158
00:08:46,931 --> 00:08:48,114
Yet Kay adores you.

159
00:08:50,099 --> 00:08:53,299
And you used to like her best
in your heart of hearts.

160
00:08:53,331 --> 00:08:57,491
You might spare me a cliche
like "heart of hearts," Dottie.

161
00:08:58,451 --> 00:09:00,179
Let me off here, please.

162
00:09:02,930 --> 00:09:04,786
Lakey, aren't you coming?

163
00:09:05,587 --> 00:09:06,835
Go ahead.

164
00:09:09,779 --> 00:09:12,114
A toast to the bride and groom.

165
00:09:12,147 --> 00:09:14,067
- Down the hatch.
- Down the hatch.

166
00:09:19,154 --> 00:09:20,498
Where's Lakey?

167
00:09:20,531 --> 00:09:23,827
She was feeling awful.

168
00:09:23,859 --> 00:09:26,674
Terrible cramps. She had to
go to the hotel and lie down.

169
00:09:26,707 --> 00:09:28,498
Is that true, Libby? True?

170
00:09:29,939 --> 00:09:31,314
Why, Kay.

171
00:09:31,347 --> 00:09:34,067
There's a little drugstore on
the corner of 59th Street.

172
00:09:34,098 --> 00:09:36,178
All the prescription whiskey you want.

173
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:38,866
Say, this Italian showed
me how to make anisette.

174
00:09:38,898 --> 00:09:40,947
You take water, straight alcohol

175
00:09:40,978 --> 00:09:43,923
and oil of anise. That gives it
the milky color like in Pernod.

176
00:09:43,954 --> 00:09:45,106
Boy!

177
00:09:45,139 --> 00:09:47,858
Kay, where did you get this man?

178
00:09:47,890 --> 00:09:50,386
I know Harald way back when,

179
00:09:50,418 --> 00:09:52,178
high school in Boise.

180
00:09:53,298 --> 00:09:55,794
Isn't Kay a honey?

181
00:09:55,826 --> 00:09:58,162
How come her parents didn't show?

182
00:09:58,194 --> 00:10:01,234
Well, I believe they sent a check
rather than make the trip, you know.

183
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,835
You're a friend of Harald's, aren't you?

184
00:10:02,866 --> 00:10:05,234
Yes...

185
00:10:05,266 --> 00:10:07,635
Since the fall of the
dollar, we occupied some

186
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:08,947
furnished rooms together.

187
00:10:10,066 --> 00:10:13,266
Or perhaps you knew that.

188
00:10:13,298 --> 00:10:17,074
An inelegant arrangement. The john, as
you girls call it, is down the hall.

189
00:10:18,386 --> 00:10:20,467
And in the closet is an electric grill.

190
00:10:20,498 --> 00:10:25,426
And hence you must excuse me if I
smell like a ham and egg sandwich.

191
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,795
And all of a sudden
she flies out of the cab.

192
00:10:27,826 --> 00:10:30,834
Well, heaven knows why she
sounded terribly off Kay.

193
00:10:30,866 --> 00:10:32,754
Well, Lakey is her own law.

194
00:10:35,026 --> 00:10:38,034
I must get the recipe for this.

195
00:10:38,066 --> 00:10:40,658
Pity a brilliant fellow like
Harald is stage managing

196
00:10:40,690 --> 00:10:42,642
instead of writing his plays.

197
00:10:42,674 --> 00:10:45,714
But in a depression, anybody
is lucky to have a job.

198
00:10:46,674 --> 00:10:48,274
I'm with Russeks myself.

199
00:10:49,074 --> 00:10:50,066
Stylist.

200
00:10:51,474 --> 00:10:54,418
You girls won't have to
scramble to jobs, I imagine.

201
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:56,626
Still, we'll all be pitching in. Yes.

202
00:10:56,658 --> 00:10:58,898
You for instance? Teaching nursery school.

203
00:10:58,930 --> 00:11:00,114
Nice.

204
00:11:00,146 --> 00:11:03,921
This stuff is very treacherous. Yeah.

205
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:05,393
Makes you quarrelsome, they say.

206
00:11:05,426 --> 00:11:07,154
I doubt that.

207
00:11:07,186 --> 00:11:09,142
Applejack's the purest thing
you can drink, you know.

208
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:10,418
It's a natural product.

209
00:11:11,634 --> 00:11:13,138
Chemistry major.

210
00:11:14,450 --> 00:11:15,730
You paint, I believe.

211
00:11:16,338 --> 00:11:18,577
I try. And you?

212
00:11:19,826 --> 00:11:22,161
I'll be in Settlement House work in Boston.

213
00:11:22,194 --> 00:11:23,506
Dottie, can I get you anything?

214
00:11:23,537 --> 00:11:25,138
No. All right.

215
00:11:29,458 --> 00:11:32,050
Kay is a very vital person, don't you think?

216
00:11:34,034 --> 00:11:38,226
Not my type however. I don't like
girls with a low center of gravity.

217
00:11:39,986 --> 00:11:42,706
I prefer the boyish figure myself.

218
00:11:42,737 --> 00:11:45,009
A narrow waist and tapering legs.

219
00:11:46,993 --> 00:11:49,778
Thin women are more sensuous.

220
00:11:49,809 --> 00:11:52,497
Scientific fact, the nerve ends
are closer to the surface.

221
00:11:52,529 --> 00:11:56,273
Lakey! Lakey, I'm so glad you're here.
You all right?

222
00:11:56,306 --> 00:11:57,681
Just fine. Why? Why?

223
00:11:57,714 --> 00:11:59,186
You were at death's door in the taxi.

224
00:11:59,217 --> 00:12:00,785
Well, I was never better.

225
00:12:00,817 --> 00:12:03,313
So, she is Lakey.

226
00:12:03,345 --> 00:12:06,705
Well, there's the little charmer herself.
Come on, you're three drinks behind.

227
00:12:06,737 --> 00:12:08,401
Kay...

228
00:12:08,434 --> 00:12:10,514
Not the Settlement House type.

229
00:12:11,857 --> 00:12:13,073
Dear no.

230
00:12:13,617 --> 00:12:14,706
Art history.

231
00:12:16,818 --> 00:12:19,185
She sails tomorrow for France, to study.

232
00:12:19,217 --> 00:12:20,306
Food, everybody.

233
00:12:45,105 --> 00:12:46,833
Baked Alaska!

234
00:12:46,865 --> 00:12:48,914
Girls, look at it.

235
00:12:48,945 --> 00:12:51,794
Childhood dreams come true, Kay.

236
00:12:51,825 --> 00:12:55,153
It's every children's party in
the whole blessed United States.

237
00:12:55,185 --> 00:12:58,321
It's Mount Whitney. It's Fujiyama.

238
00:12:58,353 --> 00:13:00,241
Libby writes, I imagine.

239
00:13:00,273 --> 00:13:02,481
She's practically set with the publisher.

240
00:13:04,529 --> 00:13:07,953
Hold it, hold it. To Harald's first play.

241
00:13:10,065 --> 00:13:11,953
Consider it as good as written.

242
00:13:11,985 --> 00:13:13,553
To Kay.

243
00:13:13,585 --> 00:13:15,217
Directing Harald's first play.

244
00:13:17,073 --> 00:13:18,833
There'll be a slight delay, girls.

245
00:13:18,865 --> 00:13:20,496
I'm starting at Macy's in the fall.

246
00:13:22,449 --> 00:13:24,241
Merchandising techniques.

